-- Blue Knights Pull Out of Bidding For Rangers, Scotsman Reports
-- B y   T i m   F a r r a n d
-- 2012-04-17T06:35:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/blue-knights-pull-out-of-bidding-for-rangers-scotsman-reports.html
The Blue Knights group, led by Paul
Murray a former director of Rangers Football Club, has pulled
out of the bidding to buy the Glasgow-based club, the Scotsman
reported, citing a statement from the Blue Knights.  The Blue Knights failed to secure funding from ticket
company Ticketus, said the newspaper, which is now in talks with
a Singapore-based company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Farrand at 
 tfarrand@bloomberg.net  